725659f-a.title: Queens: 80th Street - 60th Avenue
725659f-a.text:
80th Street, (formerly Weisse Avenue, also known as Dry Harbor
Road),west side, north of Sixtieth Avenue, showing in the foreground
at the S.W. corner of the first mentioned Street and 68th Road.the
J. Kiesel house from 1871-1891. Henry Kissel was the owner in 1923.
In the background is P.S. No. 87 a 4 story  school.
April 1923
View 2:arch 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
NAY BE REPRODUCED.
